From 2737452cd223cd5cc8a39fc013488229de237c26 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Prajw <prajw@trivartatech>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 15:34:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat: push notifications via Expo + new triggers (diary,
 assignment, fee_due)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Backend pieces of the mobile push-notification feature:

- ExpoPushService — POSTs to https://exp.host/--/api/v2/push/send with
  batching (100 per call) and DeviceNotRegistered token pruning.
- users.expo_push_token / device_platform / push_token_updated_at columns
  (FCM column kept for any non-Expo client).
- POST /mobile/device/register now accepts expo_push_token (preferred)
  alongside fcm_token.
- NotificationService::sendPushToUser dispatches to Expo + FCM in parallel;
  data payload carries {type, id, entity_id} so the mobile app can
  deep-link to the relevant screen on tap.
- New auto-fired triggers: notifyFeeDue (push channel), notifyDiary,
  notifyAssignment. Wired into the diary + assignment creation paths in
  both web (AssignmentController, StudentDiaryController) and mobile API
  (storeDiary, storeAssignment) controllers.
- Three new system templates auto-seed on next visit to Communication →
  Templates: fee_due_reminder push, diary_created, assignment_created.
- Renamed the broken notifyDiaryEntry call site to notifyDiary.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
